result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Copy of JOC from Polk County which dismisses this case.

03:31 PM Cases 20CF19, 20CM31, and 22CM27 called together.  Defendant Kacey Lynn Fischer in court with attorney Renee M Taber.  Defendant in custody, appearing from Polk County Jail.  James Jay Rennicke appeared for State of Wisconsin.  Kacey Lynn Fischer appeared by video means with Attorney.  Case 22CM27 on for status- parties indicate this matter will be DRI to def's Polk County matters, set to resolve later this week.  Cases 20CF19 and 20CM31 are on for Sentencing Hearing on Revocation.  State assures VR compliance.  Parties acknowledge receipt of ROAWs, propose no corrections or modifications.  First character witness makes a statement.  Second character witness makes a statement.  State argues for Ct 1 of 20CF19- 30 days jail, 30 on Ct 2 consecutive, Ct 4- 30 days jail consecutive; in 20CF19 30 days consecutive jail on counts 1 and 5.  Def waives all in person hearing KIV.  Defense attorney argues for time served.  Defendant makes a statement.  Discussion of charges.  Court orders: 
20CF19:
Ct 1- crim dmg- 5 months jail
Ct 2- resist- 5 months jail, concurrent to Ct 1
Ct 4- disorderly conduct- 90 days jail, concurrent to Cts 1 and 2
20CM31:
Ct 1- mistreat animal- 5 months jail, concurrent to 20CF19
Ct 5- intentionally fail- 5 months jail, concurrent to Ct 1 and 20CF19
103 days jail credit.  Remaining restitution will be converted to a civil judgment.  Appeal rights provided.  Def must pay at least $100 per month payments for 6 months, then $250 per month thereafter.
Status conference on May 17, 2022 at 03:30 pm.
